A giant crane broke free from a skyscraper, crashing into residential buildings on Manhattan's East Side, resulting in at least two deaths.
A rescue operation was underway to save those trapped.
The crane, 19 stories high, caused extensive damage as it fell.
Complaints had been made about the construction site's safety practices.
Mayor Bloomberg confirmed four deaths and multiple injuries.
Concerns were raised about the crane's safety ties prior to the incident.
Despite the tragedy, residents were thankful it occurred on a weekend.
The accident highlighted the risks associated with the city's construction boom.
